  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2006-06-28",
    "date": "2006-07-21T19:01:07Z",
    "text": "Volunteer Emergency Responder Fair Mileage Act of 2006 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) exclude from the gross income of volunteer firefighters and emergency medical responders reimbursements of automobile operating expenses incurred for the benefit of a volunteer fire department; and (2) allow such volunteers to deduct such automobile operating expenses using the higher business mileage rate instead of the standard rate."
